discovery_rule.name: assocEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: An entry associated with an association for a network service application.

item_prototype.name: assocDuration for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this association was started. If this association started prior to the last initialization of the network subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

item_prototype.name: assocApplicationType for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This indicates whether the remote application is some type of client making use of this network service (e.g., a Mail User Agent) or a server acting as a peer. Also indicated is whether the remote end initiated an incoming connection to the network service or responded to an outgoing connection made by the local application. MTAs and messaging gateways are considered to be peers for the purposes of this variable.

item_prototype.name: assocApplicationProtocol for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: An identification of the protocol being used for the application. For an OSI Application, this will be the Application Context. For Internet applications, OID values of the form {applTCPProtoID port} or {applUDPProtoID port} are used for TCP-based and UDP-based protocols, respectively. In either case 'port' corresponds to the primary port number being used by the protocol. The usual IANA procedures may be used to register ports for new protocols.

item_prototype.name: assocRemoteApplication for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The name of the system running remote network service application. For an IP-based application this should be either a domain name or IP address. For an OSI application it should be the string encoded distinguished name of the managed object. For X.400(1984) MTAs which do not have a Distinguished Name, the RFC 2156 syntax 'mta in globalid' used in X400-Received: fields can be used. Note, however, that not all connections an MTA makes are necessarily to another MTA.

discovery_rule.name: applEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: An entry associated with a single network service application.

item_prototype.name: applURL for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A URL pointing to a description of the application. This information is intended to identify and describe the application in a status display.

item_prototype.name: applDescription for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A text description of the application. This information is intended to identify and briefly describe the application in a status display.

item_prototype.name: applFailedOutboundAssociations for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The total number associations where the application entity is initiator and association establishment has failed, since application initialization. Failed associations are not counted in the accumulated association totals.

item_prototype.name: applRejectedInboundAssociations for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The total number of inbound associations the application entity has rejected, since application initialization. Rejected associations are not counted in the accumulated association totals. Note that this only counts associations the application entity has rejected itself; it does not count rejections that occur at lower layers of the network. Thus, this counter may not reflect the true number of failed inbound associations.

item_prototype.name: applLastOutboundActivity for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this application last had an outbound association. If the last association occurred prior to the last initialization of the network subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

item_prototype.name: applLastInboundActivity for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this application last had an inbound association. If the last association occurred prior to the last initialization of the network subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

item_prototype.name: applAccumulatedOutboundAssociations for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The total number of associations to the application entity since application initialization, where it was the initiator.

item_prototype.name: applAccumulatedInboundAssociations for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The total number of associations to the application entity since application initialization, where it was the responder.

item_prototype.name: applOutboundAssociations for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The number of current associations to the network service application, where it is the initiator. An outbound association occurs when this application successfully connects to another one.

item_prototype.name: applInboundAssociations for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The number of current associations to the network service application, where it is the responder. An inbound association occurs when another application successfully connects to this one.

item_prototype.name: applLastChange for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the network service application entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

item_prototype.name: applOperStatus for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Indicates the operational status of the network service application. 'down' indicates that the network service is not available. 'up' indicates that the network service is operational and available. 'halted' indicates that the service is operational but not available. 'congested' indicates that the service is operational but no additional inbound associations can be accommodated. 'restarting' indicates that the service is currently unavailable but is in the process of restarting and will be available soon. 'quiescing' indicates that service is currently operational but is in the process of shutting down. Additional inbound associations may be rejected by applications in the 'quiescing' state.

item_prototype.name: applUptime for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the network service application was last initialized. If the application was last initialized prior to the last initialization of the network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

item_prototype.name: applVersion for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The version of network service application software. This field is usually defined by the vendor of the network service application software.

item_prototype.name: applDirectoryName for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The Distinguished Name of the directory entry where static information about this application is stored. An empty string indicates that no information about the application is available in the directory.

item_prototype.name: applName for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The name the network service application chooses to be known by.
